9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 441, L.D. 1023, “Resolve, to Reestablish
10 and Continue the Work of the Blue Economy Task Force”
11 Amend the resolve by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, to Reestablish the Blue Economy Task Force to Support Maine's Emergence
13 as a Center for Blue Economy Innovation and Opportunity in the 21st Century'
14 Amend the resolve by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. Task force established. Resolved: That the Department of Economic and
16 Community Development shall convene the Blue Economy Task Force, referred to in this
17 resolve as "the task force," to support the State's emergence as a center for blue economy
18 innovation and opportunity in the 21st century.
19 As used in this resolve, "blue economy" means business sectors that rely on the
20 sustainable use of ocean resources for economic health, improved livelihoods, jobs or
21 ecosystem health, and "sustainable" means practices that support the economic growth of
22 a community while maintaining or improving the health of marine ecosystems and without
23 negatively impacting social, environmental and cultural aspects of the community.
24 Sec. 2. Task force membership. Resolved: That the task force consists of 23
25 members as follows.
26 1. The President of the Senate shall appoint one member of the Senate and the Speaker
27 of the House shall appoint 2 members of the House of Representatives, including a member
28 from each of the 2 parties holding the largest number of seats in the Legislature. Members
29 appointed by the President of the Senate and the Speaker of the House serve at the pleasure
30 of their respective appointing authority.
31 2. The Commissioner of Economic and Community Development shall appoint 19
32 members.
33 A. Members appointed by the commissioner serve at the pleasure of the commissioner
34 and must include representatives of public and private research institutions, businesses
35 that are innovating in various blue economy sectors, fisheries businesses, aquaculture
Page 1 - 132LR2011(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 441, L.D. 1023
316 businesses and equity investors in blue economy businesses. The commissioner shall
327 ensure that a majority of the members of the task force membership appointed pursuant
338 to this subsection represent a blue economy business or an entity directly involved in
349 the commercialization of blue economy-related research and innovation.
5 B. The commissioner shall to the greatest extent practicable ensure that members who
6 served on the Blue Economy Task Force, as established by Resolve 2023, chapter 119
7 and referred to in this resolve as "the prior task force," are provided an opportunity to
8 serve on the task force established by this resolve. If a member of the prior task force
9 is unable or unwilling to serve on the task force established in section 1, the
10 commissioner shall ensure that the member appointed to serve on the task force in that
11 prior member's place represents the same interests or background as the prior member.
12 3. The President of the Maine Technology Institute or the president's designee shall
13 serve as a member of the task force.
14 The appointing authorities identified in this section shall ensure that all appointments
15 are made no later than June 30, 2025.
16 Sec. 3. Chairs. Resolved: That the Commissioner of Economic and Community
17 Development shall appoint 2 cochairs from among the task force's members, one who is
18 employed by a state agency and one who is not employed by a state agency. The cochairs
19 shall set the schedule and agenda for task force meetings and preside at the meetings.
20 Sec. 4. Duties. Resolved: That the task force has, but is not limited to, the following
21 duties.
22 1. The task force shall develop recommendations for the establishment of the Center
23 for the Blue Economy, referred to in this section as "the center," which must include, but
24 is not limited to:
25 A. An organizational structure and budget for the ongoing funding of the center;
26 B. A requirement that the center be either housed within an existing institution, such
27 as the University of Maine System, or as a stand-alone, independent entity; and
28 C. The scope of the authorities and responsibilities of the center, which may include,
29 but are not limited to:
30 (1) Supporting businesses and other institutions in the State to build on the blue
31 economy advantages of and reduce the obstacles to further development of the blue
32 economy in the State identified by the prior task force in its report submitted
33 pursuant to Resolve 2023, chapter 119, section 6;
34 (2) Advancing research and development and supporting innovation in the blue
35 economy, including the financing of innovations and growth in blue economy
36 output and employment;
37 (3) Promoting communication and collaboration among blue economy institutions
38 and businesses;
39 (4) Providing common services to blue economy businesses and institutions,
40 including research support and access to journals and technologies such as
41 laboratories, 3-D printing and data management; and
Page 2 - 132LR2011(03)
