1 (5) Supporting the development of blue economy sectors as outlined in current or
2 future sector-specific development plans and roadmaps.
3 2. The task force shall recommend improvements and expansions of blue economy
4 workforce education and training to encompass the elementary and secondary school
5 system and public and private institutions of higher education.
6 Sec. 5. Staff assistance. Resolved: That the Department of Economic and
7 Community Development shall provide necessary staffing assistance to the task force. At
8 the request of the task force, other state agencies and state entities shall provide information
9 and analysis to assist the task force in its deliberations and reporting.
10 Sec. 6. Funding. Resolved: That the task force may accept grants, private
11 contributions and any other outside funding to support the task force in carrying out its
12 duties.
13 Sec. 7. Report. Resolved: That the task force shall prepare and submit a written
14 report containing its initial findings and recommendations to the Joint Standing Committee
15 on Housing and Economic Development no later than December 3, 2025. After reviewing
16 the initial report, the committee may report out legislation relating to the report to the
17 Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature. The task force shall prepare and submit
18 a written report containing its final findings and recommendations to the joint standing
19 committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over economic development matters no
20 later than November 4, 2026. After reviewing the final report, the committee may report
21 out legislation relating to the report to the 133rd Legislature in 2027.
22 Sec. 8. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
23 appropriations and allocations are made.
24 ECONOMIC AND COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT, DEPARTMENT OF
