9 SUMMARY
1100 This resolve, which is the minority report of the committee, replaces the resolve and
1111 changes the title. The amendment directs the Department of Economic and Community
1122 Development to convene the Blue Economy Task Force to develop recommendations for
1133 the establishment of the Center for the Blue Economy and other recommendations. The
1144 task force is directed to submit its report to the Joint Standing Committee on Housing and
1155 Economic Development no later than December 3, 2025 and the committee may report out
1166 legislation relating to that initial report. The task force is directed to submit its final report
1177 to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over economic
1188 development matters no later than November 4, 2026 and the committee may report out
1199 legislation relating to that final report. The amendment also provides an appropriation of
2200 $100,000 in fiscal year 2025-26 to support the Maine Technology Capacity Fund to provide
2211 matching funds in support of blue economy-related research, economic development, and
2222 education and training.
